\h #dBANHOST \d

\uUSAGE\n
#dbanhost \s[\dhostname reason\s]\d

\uDESCRIPTION\n
Dump the banned hostname database, or ban/unban a host.
When no arguments are provided, every record in the database is displayed.
To add a new record to the database (effectively toggling between banned/unbanned status), provide the hostname you wish to ban/unban, followed by a description of the reason.

For information regarding the ethical use of this command, see "help ethics".

\uEXAMPLES\n
\q#dbanhost\d to dump the database.4`
\q#dbanhost 127.0.0.1 used by Taro\d to ban/unban host "127.0.0.1".4`
